        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 8:20PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 820 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Chinook, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chinook.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
